+# The Exact-Rewrite Endpoint Window Is One Primary Exclusion Endpoint Plus One Reserve Continuation Family
+
+Status: `INFERRED` endpoint-window freeze with `VERIFIED` inherited support
+
+For Step-013 of the beyond-De Giorgi exact-rewrite chain, the honest
+theorem-facing endpoint window is not an open menu.
+
+The branch inherits only one locally frozen theorem floor:
+suitable weak solutions in the Leray-Hopf energy class with LEI, together with
+the CKN/Lin contradiction package. On that inherited floor, the primary
+endpoint family is
+
+`local concentration exclusion / endpoint-regularity exclusion on the inherited LEI / CKN ledger`.
+
+For the exact-rewrite audit, this cashes out in the branch's own fixed object:
+a candidate only earns Step-013 relevance if it improves that inherited
+exclusion ledger by lowering the effective cutoff-flux burden on
+
+`I_flux[phi] = ∬_{Q_r} (|u|^2 + 2p) u · ∇phi`
+
+inside the same shared CKN-style localized LEI package.
+
+The only honest backup is narrower and weaker in status:
+`conditional continuation / near-coercive norm-level control`, reserve only.
+It is admissible only if a later candidate already behaves like near-coercive
+norm control on that same inherited ledger. It is not a second peer theorem
+endpoint currently frozen on disk.
+
+So the Step-013 freeze blocks three kinds of drift:
+
+- reopening framework choice
+- treating continuation rhetoric as a co-primary endpoint
+- changing solution class or localization protocol while claiming an endpoint gain
+
+The solution class and localization regime remain the already-filed
+suitable-weak/LEI floor and shared CKN-style cutoff protocol. Step-013 only
+sharpens how the endpoint window sits inside that inherited package.
+
+Filed from:
+- `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-013-exploration-001-endpoint-window-solution-class-freeze.md`
